## 5. Modified Plugin Lifecycle in PluginManager

### 5.1 Updated Loading Sequence

```cpp
void PluginManager::loadPlugin(const std::filesystem::path& libPath)
{
    // 1. Open library
    auto handle = std::make_unique<PluginHandle>();
    handle->dlHandle = openLibrary(libPath);

    // 2. Check API version compatibility
    auto versionFn = loadSymbol<VersionFn>(handle->dlHandle, "mbsPluginApiVersion");
    if (versionFn && versionFn() != PLUGIN_API_VERSION) {
        throw MBSException("Incompatible plugin API version");
    }

    // 3. Resolve factory functions
    auto createFn = loadSymbol<CreatePluginFn>(handle->dlHandle, "mbsCreatePlugin");
    auto destroyFn = loadSymbol<DestroyPluginFn>(handle->dlHandle, "mbsDestroyPlugin");

    // 4. Create plugin instance
    std::unique_ptr<IPlugin> pluginPtr(createFn(), destroyFn);

    // 5. Build context
    const auto& desc = pluginPtr->descriptor();
    PluginContext ctx {
        .eventBus      = _eventBus,
        .configuration = loadPluginConfig(desc.id),
        .logger        = Logger::acquire(desc.id),
        .dataDirectory = getPluginDataDir(desc.id),
        .pluginId      = desc.id,
        .hostVersion   = currentVersion()
    };

    // 6. Initialize plugin (may subscribe to events)
    pluginPtr->initialize(ctx);

    // 7. Register HTTP routes (if any)
    if (desc.providesRoutes) {
        auto routes = pluginPtr->getRoutes();
        registerPluginRoutes(desc.id, routes);
    }

    // 8. Register tile factories (if any)
    if (desc.providesTiles) {
        auto factories = pluginPtr->getTileFactories();
        for (const auto& factory : factories) {
            _tileRegistry.registerFactory(desc.id, factory);
        }
    }

    // 9. Store handle
    handle->instance = std::move(pluginPtr);
    handle->metadata = buildMetadata(desc, libPath);
    handle->loadTimestamp = clock::now();

    // 10. Emit telemetry
    Telemetry::instance().emit("plugin.loaded", {
        {"id", desc.id},
        {"version", desc.version},
        {"providesRoutes", desc.providesRoutes},
        {"providesTiles", desc.providesTiles}
    });

    _handles.emplace_back(std::move(handle));
}
```

### 5.2 Updated Unloading Sequence

```cpp
void PluginManager::unloadPlugin(const std::string& pluginId)
{
    auto it = findPluginById(pluginId);
    if (it == _handles.end()) {
        throw MBSException("Plugin not found: " + pluginId);
    }

    auto& handle = *it;
    const auto& desc = handle->instance->descriptor();

    // 1. Unregister HTTP routes
    if (desc.providesRoutes) {
        unregisterPluginRoutes(pluginId);
    }

    // 2. Unregister tile factories
    if (desc.providesTiles) {
        _tileRegistry.unregisterFactories(pluginId);
    }

    // 3. Shutdown plugin (releases EventBus subscriptions)
    handle->instance->shutdown();

    // 4. Destroy instance
    handle->instance.reset();

    // 5. Close library
    closeLibrary(handle->dlHandle);

    // 6. Remove from collection
    _handles.erase(it);

    // 7. Emit telemetry
    Telemetry::instance().emit("plugin.unloaded", {{"id", pluginId}});
}
```

---

## 6. Summary of Required Changes

### 6.1 New Files to Create

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/interfaces/IPlugin.h` | New comprehensive plugin interface |
| `src/interfaces/PluginContext.h` | Context object for plugin initialization |
| `src/interfaces/IPluginRoute.h` | HTTP route definition structures |
| `src/core/SystemEvents.h` | Standardized system event types |

### 6.2 Files to Modify

| File | Changes |
|------|---------|
| `src/core/PluginManager.h` | Add `Server&` reference, route registration methods |
| `src/core/PluginManager.cpp` | Update `loadPlugin`/`unloadPlugin` with new lifecycle |
| `src/core/Server.h` | Expose `router()` accessor, add route removal to `Router` |
| `src/core/Server.cpp` | Implement route removal functionality |

### 6.3 Backward Compatibility

The existing `ITile` interface (`src/interfaces/ITile.h`) remains unchanged. Plugins that only provide tiles can continue using the simpler tile-factory registration pattern through the new `IPlugin::getTileFactories()` method.

---

## 7. Security Considerations

1. **Route Namespacing**: All plugin routes are automatically prefixed, preventing namespace collisions and unauthorized access to core routes
2. **Error Boundaries**: Plugin route handlers are wrapped in try-catch to prevent plugin exceptions from crashing the server
3. **Capability Flags**: Plugins must declare their capabilities, enabling host-level permission checks
4. **API Version Checking**: Incompatible plugins are rejected at load time

---

## 8. Conclusion

This design provides a clean architectural extension to MosaicBoard Studio's plugin system that:

1. **Maintains Decoupling**: Plugins interact with the system through well-defined interfaces; the `PluginManager` mediates between plugins and core components
2. **Preserves Backward Compatibility**: Existing `ITile`-only plugins continue to work
3. **Enables Deep Integration**: Plugins can now register HTTP endpoints and subscribe to system events
4. **Follows Established Patterns**: The design leverages existing patterns in the codebase (factory functions, RAII tokens, context injection)

The key insight is that `IPlugin` serves as the new "main entry point" for plugins, while `ITile` remains focused solely on visual rendering - a clean separation of concerns that scales well as plugin capabilities expand.

